\n{{Episode list \n  |EpisodeNumber   = 16 \n  |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n  |Title           = Hot Sex\n  |DirectedBy      = \n  |WrittenBy       = \n  |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15}} \n  |Viewers         =\n  |ShortSummary    = \n  |LineColor       = C4CAC4\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn April 11, 2018, it was announced that [[BET]] had given a series order to the production for a first season consisting of ten episodes. A writer and producing team had yet to be determined but the series was expected be produced by [[Paramount Television]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bennett |first1=Jessica |title=Series Based on Eddie Murphy Classic, 'Boomerang' Coming to BET |url=http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/eddie-murphy-classic-boomerang-coming-bet |website=[[Ebony (magazine)|Ebony]] |accessdate=April 11, 2018 |date=April 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Roots |first1=Kimberly |title=Boomerang: Eddie Murphy Movie Gets TV Series Adaptation at BET |url=http://tvline.com/2018/04/11/boomerang-tv-series-order-bet-adaptation-eddie-murphy/ |website=[[TVLine]] |accessdate=April 11, 2018 |date=April 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Sierra |title=BET 'Boomerang' Reboot Will Show Modern Workplace Dynamics |url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/04/boomerang-bet-reboot/ |website=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]] |accessdate=April 11, 2018 |date=April 11, 2018}}</ref> On September 24, 2018, it was announced that [[Lena Waithe]] and Ben Cory Jones would write the series' pilot episode together and executive produce alongside [[Halle Berry]] and Rishi Rajani. Jones was also expected to serve as the showrunner for the series and Dime Davis was set to direct the pilot episode. Laithe's production company Hillman Grad Productions was also slated to be involved with the series.<ref name=\"Pilot\">{{cite web |last1=Patten |first1=Dominic |title=Halle Berry & Lena Waithe Add Serious EP Spin To BET\u2019s \u2018Boomerang\u2019 Reboot |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/halle-berry-lena-waithe-boomerang-reboot-executive-producers-bet-ben-cory-jones-dime-davis-1202469809/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=September 24, 2018 |date=September 24, 2018}}</ref> On December 19, 2018, it was announced that the series would premiere on February 12, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |title=The 19 Most-Anticipated New Scripted TV Shows of 2019 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/19-anticipated-new-scripted-tv-shows-2019-1168168 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=December 26, 2018 |date=December 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn October 2018, it was announced that [[Tequan Richmond]], Tetona Jackson, Leland Martin, and Lala Milan had been cast in series regular roles and that RJ Walker, [[Paula Newsome]], Brittany Inge, [[Joey Badass|Joey BadA$$]], and Kimberly Hall would appear in a recurring capacity.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018Boomerang\u2019: Tequan Richmond & Tetona Jackson Lead Series Regular Cast Of BET Reboot |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/boomerang-tequan-richmond-tetona-jackson-lead-series-regular-cast-of-bet-reboot-1202475237/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 3, 2018 |date=October 3, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018Boomerang\u2019: RJ Walker & Paula Newsome To Recur In BET Reboot |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/boomerang-rj-walker-paula-newsome-recur-bet-reboot-1202481664/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 12, 2018 |date=October 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018Boomerang\u2019: Brittany Inge, Joey BadA$$ & Kimberly Hall To Recur in BET Series |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/boomerang-brittany-inge-joey-bada-kimberly-hall-recur-bet-reboot-1202492663/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 31, 2018 |date=October 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nPrincipal photography for the series took place from October to December 2018 in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].<ref name=\"Filming1\">{{cite web |last1=Ho |first1=Rodney |title=BET shooting \u2018Boomerang\u2019 sequel TV series 26 years later in Atlanta |url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/radiotvtalk/bet-shooting-boomerang-sequel-series-years-later-atlanta/HU7iu0vPKKFIe6uQtcQ5iP/ |website=[[Atlanta Journal Constitution]] |accessdate=December 1, 2018 |date=November 23, 2018}}</ref> In October 2018, filming took place in the [[Buckhead]] area of [[Atlanta]] and in [[East Point, Georgia|East Point]].<ref name=\"Filming1\"/> In November 2018, the series was shooting in the [[Mechanicsville, Atlanta|Mechanicsville]] neighborhood of Atlanta and on [[Ponce de Leon Avenue]] near the [[Ponce City Market]] in Atlanta.<ref name=\"Filming2\">{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=CJ |title=Here\u2019s the list of movies being filmed in Atlanta, Georgia in 2019 |url=https://atlantafi.com/heres-the-list-of-movies-being-filmed-in-atlanta-georgia-in-2019/ |website=[[AtlantaFi|Atlantafi.com]] |accessdate=March 1, 2019 |date=November 29, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Walljasper |first1=Matt |title=What\u2019s filming in Atlanta now? Undercover Brother 2, Limited Partners, Watchmen, Dolly Parton\u2019s Heartstrings, and more |url=https://www.atlantamagazine.com/news-culture-articles/whats-filming-in-atlanta-now-undercover-brother-2-limited-partners-watchmen-dolly-partons-heartstrings-and-more/ |website=Atlanta |accessdate=January 2, 2018 |date=December 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Marketing===\nOn January 6, 2019, the first trailer for the series was released.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pedersen |first1=Erik |last2=Haring |first2=Bruce |title=\u2018Boomerang\u2019 First Look: BET Comedy From EPs Lena Waithe & Halle Berry |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/boomerang-trailer-bet-comedy-lena-waithe-halle-bery-producers-1202529611/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |date=January 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Premiere===\nOn January 26, 2019, the series held a screening during the [[2019 Sundance Film Festival]]. The event was followed by a panel discussion hosted by Macro Lodge and featuring executive producer [[Lena Waithe]], showrunner Ben Cory Jones, and director Dime Davis.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Scott |first1=Sydney |title=BET Sets Up Bright Future For Primetime TV With 'Boomerang' |url=https://www.essence.com/entertainment/boomerang-bet-sundance/ |website=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]] |accessdate=February 3, 2019 |date=January 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]] season 1 has a score of 100% based on reviews from 11 critics.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/boomerang/s01</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official|https://www.bet.com/shows/boomerang}}\n* {{IMDb title|9064792}}\n\n{{BET}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boomerang (American TV series)}}\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s American comedy television series]]\n[[Category:BET original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Live action television programs based on films]]\n[[Category:Television series by Paramount Television]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Boomerang\n| image                    = \n| genre                    = [[Television comedy|Comedy]]\n| creator                  =\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Boomerang (1992 film)|Boomerang]]''|[[Barry W. Blaustein]] |& [[David Sheffield]]}}\n| director                 = \n| writer                   =\n| story                    = \n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tequan Richmond]]\n* Tetona Jackson\n* Leland Martin\n* Lala Milan\n}}\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 11 \n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lena Waithe]]\n* Ben Cory Jones\n* [[Halle Berry]]\n* Rishi Rajani\n}}\n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   =\n| runtime                  = 30 minutes\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* 606 Television\n* DeEtte Productions\n* {{nowrap|Hillman Grad Productions}}\n* [[Paramount Television Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor              = \n| network                  = [[BET]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|2|12}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}} \n| website                  = https://www.bet.com/shows/boomerang\n| website_title            = Official website\n}}\n'''''Boomerang''''' is an American [[Television comedy|comedy]] television series, based on the 1992  [[Boomerang (1992 film)|film of the same name]]. The series premiered on February 12, 2019, on [[BET]].\n\nOn April 2, 2019, it was announced that the series was renewed for a second season, which premiered on March 11, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=BET Networks Announces Second Season Pick Up for Series \"Boomerang\" and \"American Soul\"|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/04/02/bet-networks-announces-second-season-pick-up-for-series-boomerang-and-american-soul-412113/20190402bet01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=April 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n''Boomerang'' revolves around \"a successful executive who finds that his lifestyle choices have turned back on him when his new boss turns out to be a bigger deviant than he is. It is described as an updated version that explores contemporary workplace dynamics, including the changing role of gender, office politics, relationships and the conflicts between Generation X and millennials.\"<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |last1=Goldberg |first1=Lesley |title='Boomerang' Reboot Among 3 Series Orders as BET Doubles Down on Scripted (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/boomerang-reboot-3-series-orders-as-bet-doubles-down-scripted-1100776 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=April 11, 2018 |language=en |date=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Tequan Richmond]] as Bryson, based on Marcus (played by Eddie Murphy)\n* Tetona Jackson as Simone, based on Angela (played by Halle Berry)\n* Leland B. Martin as Ari, a digital producer, based on Gerald (played by David Alan Grier)\n* Lala Milan as Tia, a performance artist\n\n===Recurring===\n* RJ Walker as David Wright\n* [[Paula Newsome]] as Victoria Johnson\n* Vado As Tony\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (2019)===\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall= |season=| title= |director= |writer=  |airdate= |airdateR=<ref>{{cite web |title=Shows A-Z - boomerang on Bet |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/boomerang/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=February 25, 2019}}</ref> |viewers=  |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber   = 1\n | EpisodeNumber2  = 1 \n | Title           = Pilot\n | DirectedBy      = Dime Davis\n | WrittenBy       = [[Lena Waithe]] & Ben Cory Jones\n | OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|12}}\n | Viewers         = 0.59<ref name=\"Premiere\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-12-2019.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.12.2019|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 13, 2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 13, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2 \n |Title           = Game Night\n |DirectedBy      = Dime Davis\n |WrittenBy       = Jenny Lee \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|2|12}}\n |Viewers         = 0.54<ref name=\"Premiere\"/>\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode li