ersal Carrier]] captured by the Germans and fitted with a triple [[Panzerschreck]] mount)\n* Fahrgestell Bren (Universal Carrier reused by the Germans with a 3.7&nbsp;cm PaK 36 gun )\n* [[Leichter Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 221 Leichter Panzersp\u00e4hwagen]] Light Armoured Car\n* [[Leichter Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 222 Leichter Panzersp\u00e4hwagen]] Light Armoured Car\n* [[Leichter Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 223 Leichter Panzersp\u00e4hwagen]] Light Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 231 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (6-Rad)]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 232 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad)]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 233 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad)]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 234/1 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad)]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 234/2 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad) Puma]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 234/3 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad) Stummel]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[Schwerer Panzerspahwagen|Sd.Kfz. 234/4 Schwere Panzersp\u00e4hwagen (8-Rad)]] Heavy Armoured Car\n* [[ADGZ|Steyr ADGZ]] Heavy Armoured Car (from [[Anschluss|Austrian annex]])\n* Panzersp\u00e4hwagen P204(f) ([[Panhard 178]] captured following the [[Battle of France]])\n* Panzersp\u00e4hwagen BA-10(r) (Captured [[BA-10]])\n* Panzersp\u00e4hwagen AB43 203(i) (Captured after Italian armistice)\n\n=== Utility vehicles ===\n* [[Mercedes-Benz L3000]] truck (27,700)\n* [[Opel Blitz]] truck\n* [[Raupenschlepper, Ost]] tracked truck\n* [[Steyr 1500A]] light truck\n* [[Horch 108]] Heavy off-road passenger car, [[Einheits-PKW der Wehrmacht]] \n* [[Volkswagen K\u00fcbelwagen]] 4-piston multipurpose all-terrain support vehicle (50,435)\n* [[Volkswagen Schwimmwagen]] amphibious variant of the K\u00fcbelwagen (14,265)\n* [[Volkswagen#1937.E2.80.9345: People.27s Car project becomes K.C3.BCbelwagen|Volkswagen Type 82E]] 4-piston squad car/personal command car\n\n==== Motorcycles ====\n* [[BMW R75]] (two wheel drive motorcycle with side car)\n* [[Nimbus (motorcycle)|Nimbus]] (made in Denmark)\n* [[Z\u00fcndapp KS750]] (two wheel drive motorcycle with side car) (18,000)\n\n=== Half-tracks ===\n* [[Maultier]] (22,500)\n* [[Schwerer Wehrmachtschlepper]] (825) \n* [[Sd.Kfz. 2|Sd.Kfz. 2 \"Kettenkrad\"]] (8,345)\n* [[Maultier|Sd.Kfz. 3]] (21,020)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 4]] (1,480)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 6]] (3,660)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 7]] (12,187)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 10]] (14,000)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 250]] (6,628)\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 251]] \"Hanomag\" (15,252)\n*[[Sd.Kfz. 252|Sd.Kfz 252]] (413)\n*[[Sd.Kfz. 253|Sd.Kfz 253]] (285)\n*[[Sd.Kfz. 254|Sd.Kfz 254]] (140)\n\n===Self-propelled artillery===\n* [[Hummel self-propelled artillery|Sd.Kfz. 165 Hummel]] (100+)\n* [[Grille (self propelled artillery)|Sd.Kfz. 138/1 Grille I/II]] (389)\n* [[Wespe|Sd.Kfz. 124 Wespe]] (676)\n* [[Panzerwerfer|Sd.Kfz. 4/1 15 cm Panzerwerfer 42 auf Selbstfahrlafette \"Maultier\"]] (300)\n* [[Karl-Ger\u00e4t|Karl-Ger\u00e4t 60 cm 24 a/k/a \"M\u00f6rser Karl\"]] (7)\n* [[Landkreuzer P. 1500 Monster]] (proposed design only)\n\n===Assault guns===\n* [[Sturmgesch\u00fctz III|Sd.Kfz. 142 Sturmgesch\u00fctz III (StuG III)]] (10,086)\n* [[Sturmgesch\u00fctz III#Further variants|Sturmhaubitze 42]] (1,299)\n* [[Sturm-Infanteriegesch\u00fctz 33B]] (24)\n* [[Brummb\u00e4r|Sd.Kfz. 166 Brummb\u00e4r]] (306)\n* [[Sturmgesch\u00fctz IV|Sd.Kfz. 167 Sturmgesch\u00fctz IV (StuG IV)]] (1,108+31 conversions)\n* [[Sturmtiger]] (18)\n* [[15 cm sIG 33 (Sf) auf Panzerkampfwagen I Ausf B]] (38)\n* [[15 cm sIG 33 auf Fahrgestell Panzerkampfwagen II (Sf)]] (12)\n\n===Tank destroyers===\n* [[Panzerj\u00e4ger I]] (202)\n* [[Marder I|Sd.Kfz. 132 Marder I]] (170)\n* [[Marder II|Sd.Kfz. 131 Marder II]] (576)\n* [[Marder III|Sd.Kfz. 138 Marder III]] (1,561, all types)\n* [[Hetzer|Sd.Kfz. 138/2 Jagdpanzer 38(t) \"Hetzer\"]] (2,827)\n* [[Jagdpanzer IV|Sd.Kfz. 162 Jagdpanzer IV]] (1,977)\n* [[Nashorn|Sd.Kfz. 164 Nashorn]] (494)\n* [[Jagdpanzer V|Sd.Kfz. 173 Jagdpanzer V \"Jagdpanther\"]] (415)\n* [[Elefant|Sd.Kfz. 184 Panzerj\u00e4ger Tiger (P) Elefant]] (91)\n* [[Jagdpanzer VI|Sd.Kfz. 186 Jagdpanzer VI \"Jagdtiger\"]] (88)\n\n===Self-propelled anti-aircraft guns===\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 7]]/1 [[Flakvierling 38|2 cm FlaKvierling 38 L/112.5]] (319) - quadruple 2&nbsp;cm gun on a half track chassis\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 7]]/2 3.7&nbsp;cm FlaK 37 L/98 (123) - 3.7&nbsp;cm gun on half track chassis\n* [[Sd.Kfz. 10]]/4 and Sd.Kfz. 10/5 (~2,000) - 2&nbsp;cm gun on a half track chassis\n* [[Flakpanzer 38(t)]] (141)\n* [[M\u00f6belwagen|Flakpanzer IV \"M\u00f6belwagen\"]] (~300) - Sd.Kfz. 161/3, a 3.7&nbsp;cm gun on Panzer IV chassis\n* [[Wirbelwind|Flakpanzer IV \"Wirbelwind\"]] (87-105) - Sd.Kfz. 161/4, quadruple 2&nbsp;cm Flak on Panzer IV chassis\n* [[Flakpanzer I]] (24) - 2&nbsp;cm Flak 38 on a Panzer I chassis\n* [[Ostwind|Flakpanzer IV \"Ostwind\"]] (43\u201345) - turreted 3.7&nbsp;cm gun on Panzer IV chassis\n* [[Kugelblitz|Flakpanzer IV \"Kugelblitz\"]] (5 prototypes)\n\n===Remote controlled vehicles===\n* [[Borgward B IV]] demolition vehicle (1,181)\n* [[Goliath tracked mine]] (7,564)\n* [[Springer (tank)|Springer]] demolition vehicle (50)\n\n==Hungary==\n\n===Tanks===\n* [[38M Toldi|Toldi]] I, II, IIa, and III (202)\n* [[40M Tur\u00e1n|Turan]] I and II (424)\n\n===Self-propelled guns===\n* [[43M Zr\u00ednyi]] (40-60)\n\n===Self-propelled anti-aircraft guns===\n* [[40M Nimr\u00f3d]] (135)\n\n=== Armoured cars ===\n* [[39M Csaba]] (93)\n\n===Utility vehicles===\n* [[38M Botond]] (2,554)\n\n==Italy==\n{{See also|List of World War II weapons of Italy}}\n\n=== Tankettes ===\n* Carro Veloce [[L3/33]] (CV-33) (760)\n* Carro Veloce [[L3/35]] (CV-35) (1,740)\n\n===Tanks===\n\n==== Light tanks ====\n* [[Fiat 3000]] (200)\n* [[Fiat L6/40|Carro Armato L6/40]] (283)\n\n==== Medium tanks ====\n* [[Fiat M11/39|Carro Armato M11/39]] (100)\n* [[Fiat M13/40|Carro Armato M13/40]] (740)\n* 