pe 1 Ho-Ni I|Type 1 75&nbsp;mm SPH Ho-Ni I]] (26)\n* [[Type 1 Ho-Ni II|Type 1 105&nbsp;mm SPH Ho-Ni II]]  (54)\n* [[Type 2 Ho-I|Type 2 Gun Tank Ho-I]] (31)\n* [[Type 3 Ho-Ni III|Type 3 Gun Tank Ho-Ni III]] (31 to 41)\n* [[Type 4 Ho-Ro|Type 4 150&nbsp;mm SPH Ho-Ro]] (12)\n* [[Type 4 Ho-To|Type 4 120&nbsp;mm SPH Ho-To]] (1 prototype)\n* [[Type 5 Ho-Ru|Type 5 47&nbsp;mm SPG Ho-Ru]] (1 prototype)\n* [[Short Barrel 120 mm Gun Tank]] (12)\n* [[Naval 12 cm SPG]] (1 prototype)\n\n===Armoured personnel carriers===\n* [[Type 1 Ho-Ha]] (unknown)\n* [[Type 1 Ho-Ki]] (limited)\n* [[Type 4 Chi-So]] (limited)\n* [[Type 4 Ka-Tsu]] armoured tracked amphibious carrier (49)\n\n=== Armoured cars ===\n* [[Vickers Crossley Armoured Car]] (12)\n* [[Chiyoda armored car]] (200)\n* [[Sumida M.2593]] (1,000)\n* [[Type 93 Armoured Car]] (limited)\n\n==Netherlands==\n\n===Tankettes===\n* [[Carden Loyd tankette|Carden-Loyd Mark IV]] (5)\n* [[Marmon-Herrington CTLS]] (20)\n\n===Light Tank===\n* [[Renault FT]] (1)\n\n===Armoured cars===\n* [[Landsverk L180, L181 and L182|Landsverk L180]] (14)\n* [[Landsverk L180, L181 and L182|Landsverk L181]] (12)\n* [[M39 Pantserwagen]] (12)\n\n==New Zealand==\n\n===Converted tractors===\n* [[Bob Semple tank]] (4)\n\n===Light tanks===\n* [[Schofield tank|Light Tank, Wheel-and-Track (Schofield)]] wheel/caterpillar fast tank, prototype only\nAlso American M3 Stuart Tanks, called \"Honeys\" by the Brits and Commonwealth, used in Italy as recon vehicles\n\n=== Armoured personnel carriers ===\n* [[Universal carrier]] (1,300)\n\n=== Armoured cars ===\n* [[Standard Beaverette|Beaverette NZ]] (208) light armoured car similar to the British Beaverette\n\n==Norway==\n\n===Light tanks===\n* [[Stridsvagn L-120]] (1)\n\n==Poland==\n{{See also|list of Polish armoured fighting vehicles}}\n\n===Tankettes===\n* [[TKS|TK-3]] (280)\n* [[TKS]] (260)\n* TKS with 20&nbsp;mm gun (24)\n\n===Tanks===\n*[[4TP]]\n*[[7TP]] (162)\n*[[9TP]] (2 prototypes + 11 possible production models)\n*[[